Copper contained in ore reserves for open-pit mines is (i) the product of sulfide ore reserves and the average copper grade plus (ii) the
product of in-pit leachable reserves and the average grade of copper . Copper contained in ore reserves for under ground mines is the
product of sulfide ore reserves and the average copper grade.
